(340, 2, 2, 'Ckeck Title', 'rajesh', 'It is wrong to assume that the motion was passed by the House as the entire Opposition was opposed to the motion and, therefore', '<p>HOURS AFTER Rajya Sabha Chairman&nbsp;<a href=\"https://indianexpress.com/article/india/rajya-sabha-opposition-suspension-protests-november-30-2021-7648588/\" target=\"_blank\">M Venkaiah Naidu refused to revoke the suspension of the 12 Opposition MPs</a>, Leader of the Opposition in Rajya Sabha Mallikarjun Kharge wrote to him on Tuesday saying the suspension was an &ldquo;unprecedented excessive action&rdquo;. He also pointed out some &ldquo;anomalies&rdquo; in the motion brought by the government Monday for suspension of the members.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;It is wrong to assume that the motion was passed by the House as the entire Opposition was opposed to the motion and, therefore, cannot be the consensus of the House just because of the majority of the ruling party. The members were denied any opportunity to present their case. One of the suspended members was never referred to in the bulletin dated 11 August 2021,&rdquo; Kharge wrote.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He was referring to the case of CPI(M) member Elamaram Kareem. His name was not among the 33 MPs mentioned in the bulletin on that day for disorderly conduct.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quoting the Rules of Procedure and Conduct of Business, Kharge said the action of suspension has to be preceded by the naming of the members under the provisions of Rule 256 (1).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kharge also contested the chairman&rsquo;s argument that Rajya Sabha was a continuing institution while defending the suspension of the members for their disorderly conduct in the last session.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;I wish to state that as per Article 83 of the Constitution, the Council of State is a continuous House unlike the House of People. However, for the functioning of the House, each session is summoned by the President under Article 85 (1) of the Constitution. Thereafter, upon the completion of the sittings for that session, the House is adjourned sine die and subsequently prorogued as per the provisions of Article 85 (2)(a) of the Constitution,&rdquo; he said.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;The Monsoon Session of Rajya Sabha as summoned by the President on July 2, 2021 concluded on August 11, 2021 and was prorogued by the President on August 31, 2021. If the House had only been adjourned and then reconvened without any prorogation, the argument of continuity would merit any justification,&rdquo; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kharge urged the chairman to revoke the suspension of the MPs i</p>\r\n', '/assets/newsimagedb/1644473587.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', 'ckeck-title', '', '2022-02-10 11:43:07', '2022-02-10', '1', '1', NULL, NULL, 0),
(341, 2, 3, 'Title', 'Rajesh', 'dfghfhrfhdgfshdfsgdfsgdsfgdsfgrtghdffdghdg', '<p>sfdsfsdfsgdgfdergdfgdfsgdsgdsfsfsfeds</p>\r\n', '/assets/newsimagedb/1644476797.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', 'title', '', '2022-02-10 12:36:37', '2022-02-10', '1', '1', NULL, NULL, 0);
